    "causal_summary": "This phase came out of a live incident while deploying the 017 search work. A `memory_index_scan` with `{force:true, background:true}` was run to repair a `degraded` index. It pegged the daemon's single-thread event loop for over an hour, during which every IPC call timed out and the scan could not be cancelled, so the daemon had to be SIGKILLed.",
